<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="604" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="7.[1450,2658,260,838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="604">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1451,1801,612,641]" pageId="7" pageNumber="604">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not yet assessed on The IUCN Red List. Selous’s Spiny Mouse has never been evaluated because it was always considered a synonym of A. spinosisstmus. Due to its large distribution and high number of national parks and reserves in its distribution, Selous’s Spiny Mouse could probably be classified as Least Concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
